WEBVTT



00:00:35.181 --> 00:00:36.933
Hey!

00:00:37.016 --> 00:00:38.977
Matsu, not there. Over here.

00:00:39.060 --> 00:00:40.645
-Huh?
-Over here.

00:00:40.728 --> 00:00:43.481
-Not that way. This way.
-Ah.

00:00:48.194 --> 00:00:50.947
-Are you okay, Matsu?
-I'm not okay at all.

00:00:56.244 --> 00:00:58.371
You're really starting to look the part.

00:00:58.454 --> 00:00:59.622
You think so?

00:01:02.667 --> 00:01:06.754
I was surprised when I heard
you were coming back during the pandemic.

00:01:06.838 --> 00:01:11.050
But they do say caregiving
is physically demanding work too.

00:01:11.551 --> 00:01:14.929
I thought it'd be tough for you
to jump into manual labor,

00:01:15.013 --> 00:01:16.472
but you're keeping up well.

00:01:16.973 --> 00:01:18.433
Thank you.

00:01:23.605 --> 00:01:25.148
The boss seems happy too.

00:01:27.066 --> 00:01:28.526
Hmm, you think so?

00:01:29.569 --> 00:01:32.697
He probably just thinks
his son came tumbling back home.

00:01:33.615 --> 00:01:35.200
He may say this and that,

00:01:35.700 --> 00:01:38.536
but deep down,
having your child take over your job

00:01:38.620 --> 00:01:41.539
would make any dad happy.

00:01:41.623 --> 00:01:43.291
You're being a good son.

00:01:44.792 --> 00:01:46.044
I hope so.

00:01:47.295 --> 00:01:50.006
Okay, here we are.

00:01:50.089 --> 00:01:53.092
-Thank you, Grandma.
-Of course.

00:01:53.927 --> 00:01:55.261
All righty.

00:01:56.179 --> 00:01:57.430
Phew.

00:02:00.725 --> 00:02:03.019
-I'm home.
-Welcome back, Kanau.

00:02:04.187 --> 00:02:06.147
-I'm home.
-Welcome back.

00:02:06.231 --> 00:02:08.358
Here's a cold drink.

00:02:08.441 --> 00:02:10.235
I'm home!

00:02:10.318 --> 00:02:14.030
-We could develop a series that includes--
-I'm home!

00:02:14.530 --> 00:02:16.157
Excuse me for a moment.

00:02:16.241 --> 00:02:19.077
Here, Kanau. Go wash your hands.

00:02:19.160 --> 00:02:21.704
You know you need to wash your hands.

00:02:22.997 --> 00:02:26.417
If you don't, you won't get to eat
Grandma's hamburger steak.

00:02:26.501 --> 00:02:28.294
-Hamburger steak?
-Yeah.

00:02:31.839 --> 00:02:33.049
All right.

00:02:41.766 --> 00:02:43.559
Let's get the air out.

00:02:43.643 --> 00:02:46.312
One, two, three, four.

00:02:46.396 --> 00:02:49.440
Then, we grill it. There.

00:02:49.941 --> 00:02:51.192
And there.

00:02:51.818 --> 00:02:55.488
Careful! The oil might splatter.

00:02:55.571 --> 00:02:57.240
I wanna see!

00:02:57.323 --> 00:03:00.285
-The oil's hot. You'll get burned.
-I wanna see!

00:03:00.368 --> 00:03:03.162
Come here, Kanau. It's dangerous.

00:03:03.246 --> 00:03:05.623
-Did you do your homework?
-I'm done.

00:03:06.249 --> 00:03:09.294
I'll grill you up some tasty ones, okay?

00:03:09.377 --> 00:03:12.380
How about we go over there
and play pretend ice hockey?

00:03:12.463 --> 00:03:16.968
Sure. I'll play if you'll be the ball.

00:03:17.051 --> 00:03:20.388
What? Did you just call me a ball?

00:03:20.471 --> 00:03:22.724
You silly girl!

00:03:24.183 --> 00:03:25.935
Won't it get cramped?

00:03:26.519 --> 00:03:28.604
It'll be better for Kanau

00:03:28.688 --> 00:03:31.524
to have her own room
when she's older, right?

00:03:31.607 --> 00:03:33.318
Hurry, Mommy.

00:03:33.401 --> 00:03:35.611
-Well, that's true.
-Okay.

00:03:35.695 --> 00:03:37.405
Just under seven meters.

00:03:37.488 --> 00:03:40.116
-The problem is the entrance.
-Yeah.

00:03:44.329 --> 00:03:45.580
Sorry, just a second.

00:03:47.457 --> 00:03:48.333
Hello?

00:03:48.416 --> 00:03:51.794
Hey. How're you doing?

00:03:51.878 --> 00:03:53.588
I'm hanging in there.

00:03:53.671 --> 00:03:55.715
I've got muscle pain every day.

00:03:56.424 --> 00:03:59.552
Come on, build those muscles.
You're still young.

00:04:01.179 --> 00:04:02.680
I'll do my best.

00:04:04.349 --> 00:04:05.850
How are things over there?

00:04:05.933 --> 00:04:07.727
It's the same as always.

00:04:07.810 --> 00:04:09.062
Hmm.

00:04:09.562 --> 00:04:11.522
Well, you love working on-site.

00:04:11.606 --> 00:04:12.732
I guess.

00:04:14.942 --> 00:04:17.820
So, um…

00:04:19.489 --> 00:04:21.449
Congrats on your marriage.

00:04:23.868 --> 00:04:26.579
I told you.
It's still at the planning stage.

00:04:28.206 --> 00:04:30.958
I've been with my partner six years,
and nothing's happened.

00:04:32.543 --> 00:04:35.922
Oh? I didn't know
you wanted to get married.

00:04:36.422 --> 00:04:39.759
I do, just like everyone else.
Got a problem with that?

00:04:41.094 --> 00:04:44.180
No, not at all.

00:04:47.308 --> 00:04:48.518
When's the ceremony?

00:04:50.103 --> 00:04:51.104
Oh, no.

00:04:52.021 --> 00:04:54.482
This is for Kanau's sake.

00:04:55.566 --> 00:04:56.734
We'll just register it.

00:04:59.112 --> 00:05:00.321
I see.

00:05:01.364 --> 00:05:03.324
I'll send you a gift.

00:05:03.408 --> 00:05:05.701
No, you don't have to.

00:05:05.785 --> 00:05:06.619
Why not?

00:05:06.702 --> 00:05:08.204
It's fine.

00:05:08.704 --> 00:05:10.164
That's all I wanted to say.

00:05:10.665 --> 00:05:12.458
Come visit us once in a while.

00:05:13.167 --> 00:05:16.921
We've been short-staffed
ever since you quit.

00:05:18.339 --> 00:05:19.632
-Okay.
-Yeah.

00:05:19.715 --> 00:05:21.801
-Thank you.
-Sure.

00:05:22.385 --> 00:05:25.012
"The sky turned rosy pink,

00:05:25.096 --> 00:05:30.101
and the sun quietly rose."

00:05:30.184 --> 00:05:31.102
Okay.

00:05:31.602 --> 00:05:33.229
The end.

00:05:33.312 --> 00:05:35.148
All right. Let's go to bed.

00:05:35.231 --> 00:05:38.609
But I'm not sleepy yet.

00:05:38.693 --> 00:05:41.904
You're going shopping
with Mommy and Granny tomorrow, right?

00:05:41.988 --> 00:05:43.489
Yeah, and you too.

00:05:43.990 --> 00:05:47.952
I've got plans with Gramps tomorrow,
so I can't go.

00:05:48.035 --> 00:05:49.495
What?

00:05:50.621 --> 00:05:53.166
Okay, say goodnight to Daddy.

00:05:53.249 --> 00:05:54.333
Good night.

00:05:54.417 --> 00:05:56.836
Good. Let's go to bed then.

00:06:02.550 --> 00:06:04.051
All right.

00:06:05.553 --> 00:06:07.555
Okay, close your eyes.

00:06:09.932 --> 00:06:12.018
I'll stay here until you fall asleep.

00:06:12.101 --> 00:06:13.519
-Okay.
-Yeah.

00:06:26.032 --> 00:06:27.867
-Is she asleep?
-Yeah.

00:06:27.950 --> 00:06:29.952
She's even snoring a little.

00:06:38.753 --> 00:06:40.546
Haven't you gotten busier

00:06:40.630 --> 00:06:43.049
since you went independent
and started working remotely?

00:06:43.132 --> 00:06:46.177
Hmm, that's true.

00:06:46.677 --> 00:06:50.973
A lot of people have been
moving back home or relocating.

00:06:51.057 --> 00:06:54.310
I feel like I'm able to do more
of what I want to now

00:06:54.393 --> 00:06:56.562
than when I lived in the city.

00:06:57.522 --> 00:06:58.523
Nice.

00:07:01.108 --> 00:07:04.445
It's because you work hard for it.

00:07:07.323 --> 00:07:08.199
You think so?

00:07:08.282 --> 00:07:10.243
Of course.

00:07:16.832 --> 00:07:17.792
These were good.

00:08:00.543 --> 00:08:03.296
Let's knock this down
and build Kanau's room here.

00:08:05.715 --> 00:08:08.134
Are you sure Uncle won't get mad?

00:08:09.218 --> 00:08:10.761
It's the other way around.

00:08:11.262 --> 00:08:15.808
He's probably thrilled up there
knowing you guys are going to live here.

00:08:17.768 --> 00:08:19.395
I hope so.

00:08:20.396 --> 00:08:23.691
And you know, the funny thing about houses

00:08:23.774 --> 00:08:26.694
is that they deteriorate
when no one lives in them.

00:08:27.194 --> 00:08:31.949
I guess they get lonely
when there's no one around.

00:08:43.127 --> 00:08:46.505
Now we just have to decide
what to do with these paintings.

00:08:46.589 --> 00:08:48.215
Yeah.

00:08:52.720 --> 00:08:54.055
Hmm.

00:09:10.196 --> 00:09:11.405
What's this?

00:09:38.307 --> 00:09:39.934
It's him.

00:09:43.604 --> 00:09:48.651
Did Johan ever come by
to see you guys on his own?

00:09:49.860 --> 00:09:50.861
No.

00:09:53.239 --> 00:09:54.448
What?

00:13:16.901 --> 00:13:18.193
I wonder…

00:13:20.321 --> 00:13:22.072
what was up with him.

00:14:01.278 --> 00:14:03.447
Those were fun times.

00:14:09.912 --> 00:14:12.331
When you came to Berlin…

00:14:15.417 --> 00:14:18.003
When I got to meet Seiichi…

00:14:19.129 --> 00:14:24.802
And when the four of us lived together.

00:14:59.628 --> 00:15:01.755
It was about a year ago.

00:15:04.383 --> 00:15:05.926
Sua…

00:15:08.595 --> 00:15:10.222
reached out to me.

00:15:19.606 --> 00:15:21.233
She said Johan…

00:15:26.613 --> 00:15:28.157
is sick.

00:15:34.204 --> 00:15:35.539
Right now…

00:15:38.292 --> 00:15:40.544
he's in a hospital in Germany.

00:15:53.599 --> 00:15:54.933
I see.

00:16:01.398 --> 00:16:03.108
Kanau and I…

00:16:05.235 --> 00:16:06.862
We'll be fine.

00:16:22.836 --> 00:16:24.671
-I'm giving you medicine.
-Okay.

00:16:31.720 --> 00:16:33.013
Are you ready?

00:16:33.097 --> 00:16:35.766
Just one second.

00:16:36.725 --> 00:16:40.938
I need to do this, and then this.

00:16:43.649 --> 00:16:44.858
I got it.

00:16:48.445 --> 00:16:49.988
So, are you ready?

00:16:51.073 --> 00:16:52.199
Yeah.

00:16:53.826 --> 00:16:55.452
I'll start recording.

00:16:56.537 --> 00:16:59.373
One, two, three.

00:17:15.139 --> 00:17:16.557
I…

00:17:19.143 --> 00:17:21.770
lived my life

00:17:23.522 --> 00:17:26.608
not wanting anything…

00:17:30.988 --> 00:17:34.616
and giving up on everything.

00:17:36.660 --> 00:17:38.662
When I was 14 years old,

00:17:40.247 --> 00:17:42.166
our mother died.

00:17:43.542 --> 00:17:47.421
-Sua and I became orphans.
-Welcome home.

00:17:48.881 --> 00:17:51.091
Our relatives swarmed around

00:17:51.800 --> 00:17:57.097
for the little money our mother left us.

00:17:58.724 --> 00:18:00.475
Sua, let's eat.

00:18:00.559 --> 00:18:04.396
We couldn't trust the people
at the orphanage we were sent to either.

00:18:06.106 --> 00:18:11.111
So Sua and I decided to live on our own.

00:18:11.195 --> 00:18:13.155
You should say thank you first.

00:18:14.072 --> 00:18:15.324
Thank you.

00:18:16.033 --> 00:18:19.953
At the time, I was at rock bottom.

00:18:23.248 --> 00:18:25.667
What are you doing?

00:18:26.793 --> 00:18:28.670
You're so clumsy.

00:18:28.754 --> 00:18:34.384
While working, I began boxing at school.

00:18:35.969 --> 00:18:39.014
-This helped me distract myself.
-Finish this up.

00:18:40.349 --> 00:18:41.391
Yes, sir.

00:18:41.475 --> 00:18:43.268
Boxing was great.

00:18:44.186 --> 00:18:50.025
It's a simple world
where strength decides everything.

00:18:52.778 --> 00:18:56.907
This was around the time
I first discovered manga too.

00:19:02.829 --> 00:19:06.583
I liked stories.

00:19:06.667 --> 00:19:08.001
PHOENIX
TEZUKA OSAMU COLLECTION

00:19:08.085 --> 00:19:10.295
They were a world of my own.

00:19:12.631 --> 00:19:14.216
But reality…

00:19:14.716 --> 00:19:17.844
Try hitting me.
You're just a little shrimp.

00:19:17.928 --> 00:19:19.304
…was different.

00:19:19.805 --> 00:19:23.934
It's his fault!
Why's he giving me all the work?

00:19:24.017 --> 00:19:25.978
No one ever complains to him!

00:19:26.061 --> 00:19:28.814
I used to think everyone else was trash.

00:19:30.482 --> 00:19:33.402
And they were.

00:19:37.197 --> 00:19:39.616
You all do so well
with your parents around.

00:19:43.745 --> 00:19:46.123
Sorry, excuse me.

00:19:46.206 --> 00:19:48.375
Who can solve this problem?

00:19:50.961 --> 00:19:52.004
Anyone?

00:19:53.046 --> 00:19:54.965
-Me.
-Miss Hwang Sua.

00:19:57.718 --> 00:20:00.429
-I'll answer from here.
-Go ahead.

00:20:01.596 --> 00:20:04.349
X is negative 7 over 11.

00:20:04.433 --> 00:20:08.770
You managed to calculate it in your head.
Everyone, let's give her a hand.

00:20:08.854 --> 00:20:10.647
Within that reality,

00:20:11.440 --> 00:20:15.652
Sua was my pride and my hope in life.

00:20:18.613 --> 00:20:20.782
Sua really wants to study abroad.

00:20:22.784 --> 00:20:23.827
Study abroad?

00:20:24.745 --> 00:20:28.332
She's a genius. A truly remarkable one.

00:20:28.415 --> 00:20:29.833
She's far too talented

00:20:29.916 --> 00:20:33.962
for the top high schools
and universities around here.

00:20:44.890 --> 00:20:46.975
She should go to a gifted school.

00:20:49.061 --> 00:20:53.273
If she does well,
she'll get a scholarship to study abroad.

00:20:55.901 --> 00:20:58.111
Here's a brochure
for overseas universities.

00:21:02.366 --> 00:21:05.535
It's not bad to rely on adults
once in a while.

00:21:11.625 --> 00:21:12.626
Johan.

00:21:13.460 --> 00:21:18.298
Through boxing,
you can make both your dreams come true.

00:21:18.382 --> 00:21:19.716
This person…

00:21:20.217 --> 00:21:23.011
-Let's give it a try.
-Can I trust him?

00:21:23.095 --> 00:21:27.682
It was the first time
I felt this way about someone.

00:21:31.853 --> 00:21:36.316
Already gassed? And you're the punk
who lost his college spot over a fight?

00:21:36.400 --> 00:21:37.734
You're gonna be champion.

00:21:37.818 --> 00:21:41.530
Your fists are sending your sister
to study abroad, aren't they?

00:21:54.126 --> 00:21:55.127
Last one!

00:21:59.798 --> 00:22:02.300
-Are you okay, Mr. Kang?
-Shut up.

00:22:05.262 --> 00:22:06.096
Let's go again.

00:22:06.179 --> 00:22:11.977
Put more power into it. Good. More!

00:22:12.060 --> 00:22:15.105
Finish it up!

00:22:15.730 --> 00:22:19.234
IS THE USUAL PLACE OKAY?

00:22:19.317 --> 00:22:20.318
OKAY.

00:22:20.402 --> 00:22:21.361
One more time!

00:22:22.821 --> 00:22:25.073
Wow, you're working hard.

00:22:29.911 --> 00:22:32.873
Johan, you're working on Christmas Day?

00:22:32.956 --> 00:22:35.792
Yeah, but I have
an important appointment before that.

00:22:35.876 --> 00:22:37.002
Bye then.

00:22:48.346 --> 00:22:51.349
What did you just say?

00:22:52.517 --> 00:22:56.688
Why don't you quit boxing?

00:22:57.522 --> 00:23:00.650
I think getting a stable job

00:23:00.734 --> 00:23:03.653
would be better for Sua's sake too.

00:23:08.033 --> 00:23:09.034
Well,

00:23:10.410 --> 00:23:16.917
you were the one who told me
to chase both our dreams.

00:23:23.381 --> 00:23:24.591
Yeah.

00:23:26.384 --> 00:23:27.594
That's true.

00:23:31.097 --> 00:23:33.099
That's exactly why I'm saying this.

00:23:35.685 --> 00:23:37.938
I was wrong.

00:23:38.021 --> 00:23:42.317
Dreams? Ideals? Do they even exist?

00:23:43.026 --> 00:23:47.280
After ten years of teaching,
I finally understand.

00:23:56.873 --> 00:23:58.333
Johan.

00:23:59.626 --> 00:24:05.840
Focus on what you can stick with,
rather than what you want to do.

00:24:08.969 --> 00:24:12.013
You can take it easy now.

00:24:13.265 --> 00:24:15.141
Let the weight off your shoulders.

00:24:16.518 --> 00:24:20.647
Living in reality isn't so hard.

00:24:22.274 --> 00:24:25.360
I'm going to quit teaching.

00:24:27.362 --> 00:24:30.115
I felt that I needed to tell you this.

00:24:31.741 --> 00:24:34.452
This will be the last time
I stick my nose in.

00:24:37.247 --> 00:24:39.666
I had tried to live the best I could.

00:24:41.543 --> 00:24:44.379
I thought I had met an adult
that I could look up to.

00:24:45.922 --> 00:24:47.924
But even that person…

00:24:50.051 --> 00:24:52.178
was knocked down by reality.

00:24:54.681 --> 00:24:58.310
And he walked away from me.

00:24:58.893 --> 00:25:01.021
AVAILABLE BALANCE
30,350 WON

00:25:01.104 --> 00:25:03.231
Are some people
never meant to be rewarded…

00:25:05.650 --> 00:25:07.652
no matter what they do?

00:25:13.700 --> 00:25:15.118
Besides,

00:25:15.619 --> 00:25:20.582
what am I even struggling for?

00:25:23.501 --> 00:25:28.131
Why am I trying so hard
to live a good life?

00:25:30.592 --> 00:25:31.968
Welcome.

00:25:42.395 --> 00:25:44.105
The next drink is on me.

00:25:47.734 --> 00:25:50.153
I'm Shim Gicheol, a boxing promoter.

00:25:50.654 --> 00:25:52.113
Uh…

00:25:53.448 --> 00:25:55.867
I might be able to help you.

00:25:59.663 --> 00:26:00.914
Please, have a seat.

00:26:00.997 --> 00:26:02.165
The devil's whispers.

00:26:02.248 --> 00:26:04.876
-Two of the same drink, please.
-Yes, sir.

00:26:05.794 --> 00:26:07.545
Their timing is impeccable.

00:26:08.046 --> 00:26:09.047
Take a seat.

00:26:12.133 --> 00:26:13.802
How are you still an amateur?

00:26:13.885 --> 00:26:15.637
Because of this timing…

00:26:18.098 --> 00:26:24.020
the voice I'd normally ignore
reached my ears.

00:26:25.730 --> 00:26:28.817
From just three matches,

00:26:29.734 --> 00:26:35.573
I earned dozens of times more
than I did in my entire boxing career.

00:26:36.991 --> 00:26:37.826
Do a good job.

00:26:39.160 --> 00:26:42.539
-But I'm not sure why.
-Yes, sir.

00:26:43.039 --> 00:26:46.334
This was supposed to be
what I wanted, but…

00:27:44.851 --> 00:27:46.060
I'm sorry.

00:27:47.604 --> 00:27:48.605
I…

00:27:50.106 --> 00:27:53.026
I was scared of being liked.

00:28:04.078 --> 00:28:05.079
Dammit.

00:28:11.377 --> 00:28:15.298
I could tell right away
from looking at his eyes.

00:28:17.258 --> 00:28:18.384
We're the same.

00:28:18.468 --> 00:28:22.347
-Why is it always me? Why?
-He's just like me.

00:28:34.192 --> 00:28:35.610
Hey, wait!

00:28:47.997 --> 00:28:51.125
What I saw back then felt very strange.

00:28:51.918 --> 00:28:57.048
He looked like
he was trying to accept something.

00:28:57.131 --> 00:29:00.176
Something I could never
come to terms with.

00:29:00.677 --> 00:29:01.511
Hey!

00:29:01.594 --> 00:29:06.975
In that instant,
I knew I didn't want him to die.

00:29:07.684 --> 00:29:09.727
I don't know why I did it.

00:29:11.020 --> 00:29:14.023
My actions weren't logical.

00:29:15.149 --> 00:29:17.026
But thinking back on it now…

00:29:17.110 --> 00:29:17.944
Hey.

00:29:18.027 --> 00:29:21.239
…I think my heart

00:29:22.156 --> 00:29:25.243
had already been touched at that point.

00:29:31.958 --> 00:29:33.334
That's why…

00:29:39.924 --> 00:29:42.343
Don't run, Hwang Johan!

00:29:42.844 --> 00:29:45.346
…when I heard that voice in the ring,

00:29:47.140 --> 00:29:49.767
from a guy I thought I'd never see again,

00:29:51.269 --> 00:29:55.481
it honestly sounded like
the voice of salvation.

00:29:56.816 --> 00:30:01.779
In that voice, I found comfort.

00:30:05.116 --> 00:30:06.784
Good work.

00:30:20.423 --> 00:30:22.133
RYU: GOOD LUCK.

00:30:22.216 --> 00:30:23.843
"Good luck"? Is he for real?

00:30:25.261 --> 00:30:30.558
I think he painted it while thinking
of someone special to him.

00:30:38.942 --> 00:30:40.818
You were trying to protect it, right?

00:30:40.902 --> 00:30:42.528
Your soul.

00:30:44.238 --> 00:30:46.658
It definitely felt like a miracle.

00:30:53.539 --> 00:30:54.832
This is delicious.

00:31:00.964 --> 00:31:05.009
His feelings get hurt easily.

00:31:06.219 --> 00:31:11.140
And he thinks of himself as a weak person.

00:31:12.600 --> 00:31:17.271
But being able to feel hurt

00:31:18.481 --> 00:31:20.149
is an incredible thing.

00:31:21.651 --> 00:31:27.198
People who give up and drift through life…

00:31:30.493 --> 00:31:32.370
don't feel pain anymore.

00:31:34.205 --> 00:31:36.749
They're afraid of getting hurt…

00:31:39.085 --> 00:31:41.462
so they run away.

00:31:41.546 --> 00:31:43.589
-You asked me to come to Japan.
-What?

00:31:43.673 --> 00:31:45.174
Don't look down on me.

00:31:45.258 --> 00:31:48.177
But you still let yourself get hurt.

00:31:49.429 --> 00:31:52.557
And you haven't given up

00:31:54.475 --> 00:31:58.271
on getting involved with people.

00:31:58.354 --> 00:32:00.481
-Ta-da. How is it?
-You're strong.

00:32:00.565 --> 00:32:05.069
-Whoa, that's good!
-You're a really strong person.

00:32:05.570 --> 00:32:07.280
-It looks like you.
-Does it?

00:32:08.239 --> 00:32:09.240
I…

00:32:13.119 --> 00:32:17.665
I changed because I was with Ryu.

00:32:19.542 --> 00:32:20.752
No.

00:32:23.212 --> 00:32:25.089
I was able to change myself.

00:32:28.468 --> 00:32:33.765
If I had told him about my illness…

00:32:40.730 --> 00:32:47.361
knowing Ryu, he probably would have
insisted on taking care of me.

00:32:50.156 --> 00:32:51.574
But you know…

00:32:55.244 --> 00:32:56.454
that…

00:32:59.290 --> 00:33:02.126
wasn't the happiness I wanted for him.

00:33:08.257 --> 00:33:09.133
But…

00:33:18.601 --> 00:33:20.603
I wanted you by my side when I died.

00:33:24.440 --> 00:33:27.902
I wanted you to be part of the last sight…

00:33:34.158 --> 00:33:36.369
I would ever see in this world.

00:33:52.468 --> 00:33:56.722
I'm glad you were able to meet Ryu.

00:34:29.755 --> 00:34:30.756
Hey.

00:34:34.552 --> 00:34:35.970
Why?

00:34:39.307 --> 00:34:41.517
Why are you here?

00:34:44.812 --> 00:34:49.859
If you're here…

00:34:51.944 --> 00:34:53.279
it makes me…

00:34:56.741 --> 00:34:59.493
want to live longer.

00:35:48.793 --> 00:35:50.419
We'll be off then.

00:35:55.091 --> 00:35:56.092
Bye.

00:36:14.777 --> 00:36:19.824
You finally found
what you were looking for.

00:36:23.452 --> 00:36:25.871
You said softly…

00:36:32.295 --> 00:36:34.005
"This long journey…

00:36:36.674 --> 00:36:38.175
is almost over."

00:36:54.692 --> 00:36:58.946
I've met a lot of people until now.

00:37:01.824 --> 00:37:05.119
And of those people,
there are some I can't see anymore.

00:37:09.999 --> 00:37:11.625
You said to me…

00:37:15.212 --> 00:37:17.757
"You have a lonely look
on your face again."

00:37:20.718 --> 00:37:26.182
"Loneliness is an incredible invention."

00:37:26.682 --> 00:37:27.683
We're here.

00:37:30.603 --> 00:37:32.480
"Because feeling lonely means

00:37:34.065 --> 00:37:36.442
there's someone you truly care about."

00:37:38.694 --> 00:37:40.905
"Someone you really want to see."

00:37:44.867 --> 00:37:46.619
How's Kanau?

00:37:49.413 --> 00:37:50.331
I'll show you.

00:37:53.125 --> 00:37:55.544
"That's truly amazing."

00:37:57.046 --> 00:37:57.963
A face mask.

00:37:58.047 --> 00:37:59.382
"You know that, right?"

00:38:08.474 --> 00:38:10.184
I nodded.

00:38:11.852 --> 00:38:13.854
Tears welled up in my eyes.

00:38:15.356 --> 00:38:17.358
She's starting to look like Seiichi.

00:38:17.441 --> 00:38:18.275
Then…

00:38:18.359 --> 00:38:19.318
And Sumiko's upset.

00:38:19.402 --> 00:38:24.990
…the tears soaked up the light
and turned into beautiful crystals.

00:38:33.249 --> 00:38:37.795
I cry because
whenever I looked at something,

00:38:39.422 --> 00:38:42.383
you were always by my side,
watching it with me.

00:38:47.721 --> 00:38:50.266
And when you are looking at something,

00:38:51.517 --> 00:38:56.188
I would want to look at it too,
right by your side.

00:39:01.610 --> 00:39:06.240
We've seen so much together.

00:39:14.290 --> 00:39:16.459
That came out of nowhere.

00:39:23.466 --> 00:39:25.134
It's a great story, isn't it?

00:39:32.099 --> 00:39:35.060
It's my story.

00:39:45.613 --> 00:39:49.825
So, wherever we are,
no matter what we're doing,

00:39:49.909 --> 00:39:51.869
we're never alone.

00:40:10.513 --> 00:40:13.724
Where should we go next?

00:40:15.809 --> 00:40:17.436
Anywhere's fine.

00:40:19.063 --> 00:40:20.481
As long as I'm with you.

00:40:24.235 --> 00:40:25.653
Saranghae.

00:40:27.988 --> 00:40:29.365
I love you.

00:42:48.170 --> 00:42:51.090
Subtitle translation by: Remi Miura